Peter Obi, the presidential candidate of the Labour Party (LP), on Monday, delivered a speech at Chatham House in London. The former Anambra governor spoke on ‘Nigeria’s 2023 Elections: A Vision for Policy Change and Institutional Reforms’. Datti Baba-Ahmed, his running mate; Pat Utomi, professor of political economy, and Julius Abure, LP chairperson, were also in attendance. Below are photos.         